  "identifier": "concrete",
  "description": "One-step continuous-time Targeted Minimum Loss-Based Estimation (TMLE) for outcome-specific absolute risk estimands in right-censored survival settings with or without competing risks. Treatment estimation uses SuperLearner, and event-specific hazard candidate libraries can include Cox, Coxnet, random survival forests, additive hazards, and HAL with cross-validated discrete selection.",
  "name": "concrete: Continuous-Time Competing Risks Estimation using TMLE",
